maven-archetype-quickweb
========================
Failed experiment to create an alternative to maven-archetype-quickstart that would create a fuller directory layout to start with. For example:

my-app
|-- pom.xml
|-- src
|   -- main
|      -- resources
|      -- java
|         -- com
|            -- shaunabram
|   -- test
|      -- resources
|      -- java
|         -- com
|            -- shaunabram
|               -- AppTest.java
|   -- webapp
|      -- index.jsp
|      -- WEB-INF
|         -- web.xml

Originally copied from: http://svn.apache.org/repos/asf//maven/archetypes/trunk/maven-archetype-quickstart/
After seeing this stackover flow posting: http://stackoverflow.com/questions/12634890/maven-archetype-quickstart-with-resources-folder
This posting helped: http://stackoverflow.com/questions/13499873/how-to-use-my-custom-archetype-with-maven
And after running: mvn install archetype:update-local-catalog
I can see it show up in .m2, but when I run: mvn archetype:generate -DarchetypeCatalog=local
I get an error saying:
